  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pull out the middle stalk from each mushroom and keep for\nanother time (fry in butter and have with scrambled eggs). Put\nthe mushrooms, hole-side-up, on a large baking tray and dollop\na spoonful of pesto into each hole. Cut the goat’s cheese logs\ninto four rounds each (to give eight rounds in total) and plonk one\nround onto each mushroom. Drizzle with olive oil and season with\nsalt and black pepper. Place under the hot grill for 8 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, halve the cherry tomatoes and mix these with the\nsalad leaves in a mixing bowl. Drizzle with a little olive oil and\nseason with salt, pepper and balsamic vinegar to taste. Divide the\nsalad between four plates."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get a frying pan over a medium heat. Add the pine nuts and toast\nuntil golden brown, shaking occasionally, then turn off the heat."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Use a fish slice or spatula to put two grilled mushrooms on top of\neach salad and scatter over the toasted pine nuts to serve."
    }
  ],
